Sprint 4 – Reflection Log
What went well:

The sprint delivered a key infrastructure milestone by migrating the application from a local MongoDB instance to MongoDB Atlas.

Database connectivity and environment configuration were stabilised, providing a reliable foundation for later development.

Re-scoping the sprint helped reduce the risk of future rework and ensured later features can be built on a stable backend.

Even better if:

Sprint goals had been planned with clearer consideration of task dependencies, particularly where frontend and deployment tasks relied on backend infrastructure.

The sprint backlog had focused more narrowly on infrastructure tasks rather than combining them with feature delivery.

How we can improve:

Sprint goals will be reviewed more consistently to ensure they are realistic and dependency-aware.

Objectives will be defined more clearly and aligned with the SMART criteria, with less overlap between tasks.

Any re-scoping will be documented more clearly in future sprint reviews.
